Evaluate Participant Eligibility With Prescreening Assessments

Accelerate research study timelines by swiftly identifying participants who meet the eligibility criteria for clinical trials. You can configure the built-in Omnistudio components to enable prescreening assessments for participants to quickly determine their eligibility by responding to a few predefined questions. Make these assessments available on your Experience Cloud site. You can also encourage non-eligible candidates to share contact information for future trials.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience in Enterprise and Unlimited editions with Life Sciences Cloud and Participant Enrollment Add-On license.

When: Participant Management is available starting in June 2024.

Who: This feature is available to users with Health Cloud Starter, Omnistudio admin, and Omnistudio User permission set licenses.

How: From Setup, find Prefill Assessment Question Settings, turn on Prefill Assessment Questions, and then create assessment question records. To activate candidate eligibility, create a version of the built-in Omniscript and add it to the care program details record. Next, create a version of the built-in integration procedure. In the business rules engine settings, create and configure an expression set. Next, create a version of the built-in integration procedure for eligibility results and add the expression set you created to this integration procedure. Finally, add these components to your experience cloud site.
